{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place coconut sugar into mixing bowl and mill <b>30 sec\/speed 10<b> or until a very fine consistency. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 200 g of the water and cook <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>.","Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh remaining 100 g water into it. Add gelatine and stir to combine until gelatine has completely dissolved and liquid is slightly thick."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong> <strong>.<\/strong> Add gelatine mixture to mixing bowl, ensuring it is poured over sugar syrup and not onto blades, and mix <b>2 min\/speed 2<b>. Leave mixture to cool in mixing bowl with lid removed until it reaches 37°C (approx. 1 hour) (see Tips).","Grease and line a square baking tin (20 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Add cream of tartar to mixing bowl and whip <b>5 min\/speed 4<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong> <strong>.<\/strong> ","Transfer mixture into prepared dish, then place into refrigerator to set overnight. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Remove marshmallow from dish and cut into squares (approx. 3 x 3 cm). Roll in arrowroot flour to coat, then transfer into a sealable container and set aside until ready to decorate.","Place chocolate of choice into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 9<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and melt <b>3 min\/50°C\/speed 2<b> or until melted. Transfer into a bowl.","Thread marshmallows onto skewers, and dip into chocolate until completely coated, allowing excess to drip off marshmallows. Spoon coconut (optional) or 100s and 1000s (optional) over chocolate dipped marshmallows, until completely coated on all sides. Serve immediately or transfer into a sealable container and place into refrigerator until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g coconut sugar","300 g warm water","2 tbsp gelatine powder","oil, for greasing","2 pinches cream of tartar","2 - 3 tbsp arrowroot flour, for dusting","400 - 500 g dairy free chocolate, broken into pieces (dark, white or milk)","50 - 150 g shredded coconut, for decorating (optional)","2 - 3 tbsp gluten free 100s and 1000s sprinkles, for decorating (optional) (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r119235","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-cFBNmduM4O0\/XZWcghW-ZsI\/AAAAAAAAeao\/Iy4yhRJiDeYEQS3_WmDgU4JD5bi3CLQ1gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_0AiKzJc0raZ3VfJg.png","title":"Marshmallow pops","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"7.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"21.7 g","calories":"669 kJ \/ 159 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, deep-sided baking dish (20 cm), square baking tray (20 cm), sealable container, bowl, wooden skewers, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["To check the temperature of the contents in the mixing bowl, remove then replace mixing bowl - your Thermomix will tell you the temperature in the bowl.","You can make the marshmallows and dust them without turning them into pops. Simply serve after cutting into squares and dusting.","If uncoated, marshmallows will last up to 1 week in a sealable container. If coated with chocolate, store in the refrigerator in a sealable container for up to 1 week.","It is best to have the melted chocolate on the thicker side so it doesn't drip too much. If chocolate gets too thick while coating, transfer back into the mixing bowl and re-heat.","This recipe uses Hopper gluten free natural 100s and 1000s sprinkles."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","25h 40m","35 portions"]}